# Onshape Parts

A **part** is a single solid body produced by a Part Studio. The `parts` group is
read-only: it enumerates the bodies in an element and exposes per-body geometry,
mass, and export endpoints. It never builds geometry — that is the Part Studio's
job (@onshape/partstudios). A part is addressed by a `partId` scoped to one element.

## Model

- Path family is `…/parts/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}` where `{wvm}` is the
  literal `w`/`v`/`m` and `{wvmid}` the matching id (see @onshape/api for the did/wid/eid model).
  Every endpoint here is a `GET`, so a version (`/v/`) or microversion (`/m/`)
  works as well as a workspace (`/w/`).
- A **Part Studio** is the element (`eid`) that *makes* parts; listing parts in
  that element returns one entry per resulting solid body. The Part Studio's
  feature tree is at `…/partstudios/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}/features`
  (@onshape/partstudios) — `parts` is the consumed-geometry view of the same
  element.
- **`partId`** (field `partId`, e.g. `"JHD"`) identifies a body *within* one
  element; it is stable across microversions of that element but not globally
  unique. Most per-part endpoints take it as `…/partid/{partid}/…`. `name` is the
  human label ("Part 1"); `bodyType` is `solid`/`sheet`/`wire`/`mesh`.
- Geometry endpoints accept tolerances (`angleTolerance`, `chordTolerance`,
  `maxFacetWidth`) and a `configuration` string to evaluate a configured variant.
  STL/Parasolid/glTF here are **synchronous** exports (the response body is the
  file); the async/translation route is @onshape/export_translation.

## Endpoints

| METHOD path | purpose |
|---|---|
| `GET /parts/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}` | all parts in a document (workspace/version/microversion) |
| `GET /parts/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}` | all parts in one element |
| `GET …/e/{eid}/partid/{partid}/massproperties` | part mass properties (volume, mass, COM, inertia) |
| `GET …/e/{eid}/partid/{partid}/boundingboxes` | axis-aligned bounding box (low/high X/Y/Z, metres) |
| `GET …/e/{eid}/partid/{partid}/bodydetails` | B-rep body details (faces/edges/vertices topology) |
| `GET …/e/{eid}/partid/{partid}/tessellatedfaces` | triangulated faces (facet points, normals) |
| `GET …/e/{eid}/partid/{partid}/tessellatededges` | polyline-tessellated edges |
| `GET …/e/{eid}/partid/{partid}/stl` | synchronous STL export (`application/octet-stream`) |
| `GET …/e/{eid}/partid/{partid}/parasolid` | synchronous Parasolid export |
| `GET …/e/{eid}/partid/{partid}/gltf` | synchronous glTF export (`model/gltf+json`) |
| `GET …/e/{eid}/partid/{partid}/shadedviews` | rendered shaded images (base64) |
| `GET …/e/{eid}/partid/{partid}/sheetmetal/bendtable` | sheet-metal bend table (sheet-metal parts only) |

## Shapes

**List parts** — `GET /parts/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}` → array; one object per
body (trimmed to the load-bearing fields):

```json
[
  {
    "partId": "JHD",
    "name": "Part 1",
    "bodyType": "solid",
    "elementId": "a77918b06d5131918477a269",
    "microversionId": "…",
    "partNumber": "",
    "isHidden": false,
    "isMesh": false,
    "material": { "...": "BTPartMaterialInfo" },
    "appearance": { "...": "BTPartAppearanceInfo" }
  }
]
```

**Bounding box** — `GET …/partid/{partid}/boundingboxes` → all values in metres,
in the part's coordinate system:

```json
{ "lowX": -0.025, "lowY": -0.025, "lowZ": 0.0,
  "highX": 0.025, "highY": 0.025, "highZ": 0.01 }
```

`massproperties` returns `{ "bodies": { "<partId>": { volume, mass, centroid,
inertia, … } }, "microversionId": "…" }` (per spec; same body shape as
@onshape/massproperties).

## Recipe

Read-only. List parts in the kb2 element, read back a `partId`+`name`, then
re-query that part. Basic auth (`access:secret` over HTTPS, local testing only —
production uses HMAC, see @onshape/auth).

```bash
DID=378e93b0ad360aa043a0220b
WID=09273312fedee7bf3c3482ad
EID=a77918b06d5131918477a269
BASE=https://cad.onshape.com/api/v10
AUTH="$ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY:$ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY"

# list parts in the element
curl -sS -u "$AUTH" -H 'Accept: application/json' \
  "$BASE/parts/d/$DID/w/$WID/e/$EID" | tee parts.json

# verify: pull the first part's id + name
PID=$(jq -r '.[0].partId' parts.json)
jq -r '.[0] | "part \(.partId) = \(.name) [\(.bodyType)]"' parts.json
test -n "$PID" && [ "$PID" != "null" ] || { echo "no parts found"; exit 1; }

# follow-up GET on that partId — bounding box (metres) confirms the part resolves
curl -sS -u "$AUTH" -H 'Accept: application/json' \
  "$BASE/parts/d/$DID/w/$WID/e/$EID/partid/$PID/boundingboxes" | jq .
```

The list step returning a non-empty array with a readable `partId`/`name`, and the
follow-up box returning finite `low*`/`high*`, confirms the round-trip. For
mass/inertia detail see @onshape/massproperties; for the Part Studio that built
these bodies @onshape/partstudios; for `partNumber`/custom-property fields
@onshape/metadata; for async/foreign-format export @onshape/export_translation.
UI fallback (visual check of a body): @onshape/playwright.
